(75, 1, '2018-08-25 00:23:32', '2018-08-25 00:23:32', '<h2>What isÂ <em>frank?</em></h2>\r\n<i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">frank</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is more than just a gathering. It is an essential community for movement builders and change makers â the people who use communications to drive positive social, institutional and behavioral change. A part of the University of Florida Center for Public Interest Communications, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">frank</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> gathering informs and drives the field of public interest communications</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Â through research, insights and news</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now in its sixth year, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">frank</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is bringing changemakers together from across the earth. Our community is made up of strategists, researchers, artists, journalists, students, activists and more. From corporate advocacy to the research lab, to the grassroots on the street activist, the </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">frank </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">community believes in using evidence-based strategies to drive social change. If you see yourself in our mission, then we welcome you into our community.</span>\r\n<h2>Why are we called â<em>frank</em>â?</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">â</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">frank</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">â not only refers to our direct and candid approach to our work in public interest communications, it pays homage to <a href=\"https://allisoncandreva.com/test/about/who-is-frank-karel/\">Frank Karel</a></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, the big thinker who invested so much in building the field for people who use strategic communications to drive social change.</span>', 'what is <em>frank</em>?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'what-is-frank', '', '', '2018-10-05 00:41:27', '2018-10-05 00:41:27', '', 2, 'https://allisoncandreva.com/test/?page_id=75', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(77, 1, '2018-08-25 00:24:01', '2018-08-25 00:24:01', '<h2>Who is Frank Karel?</h2>\r\nAs a leader who spent his 30-year career using communication for social change, and as vice president for communications for theÂ <a href=\"http://www.rwjf.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Robert Wood JohnsonÂ </a>andÂ <a href=\"https://www.rockefellerfoundation.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Rockefeller Foundations</a>, Frank recognized the critical importance of strategic communication in taking on the worldâs most important challenges.\r\n\r\nHis vision nurtured and grew our field. SoÂ <em>frank</em>Â refers not only to the candor and directness with which we approach our work but also to our affection for him.\r\n\r\nAs part of his vision to build the field of public interest communications, Frank and his wife, Betsy, endowed a chair in public interest communications at his beloved alma mater, theÂ <a href=\"https://www.jou.ufl.edu/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">College of Journalism and Communications</a>Â at theÂ <a href=\"http://www.ufl.edu/\">University of Florida</a>. The chair is responsible for building a curriculum inÂ public interest communications, mentoring and advising students who plan to build careers in the field, identifying connections with other fields, establishing community among those who work in public interest communications and building the community of scholars whose research will help to establish public interest communications as a discipline.', 'who is Frank Karel?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'who-is-frank-karel', '', '', '2018-10-06 01:48:42', '2018-10-06 01:48:42', '', 2, 'https://allisoncandreva.com/test/?page_id=77', 1, 'page', '', 0),
